      "name": "FDA centrifugal pump hemolysis experimental dataset — Q4 2025 freeze",
      "description": "In-vitro hemolysis index measurements collected at five flow-speed operating points on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump test rig. Data were frozen for model validation on 2025-10-17, approximately three weeks before the turbulence-model coefficient update (2025-11-10) that altered near-wall shear layer predictions. The assessment team noted the revision was limited to the Wilcox k-omega beta* coefficient and argued it would not materially affect bulk hemolysis index comparisons; no formal re-validation run was executed against the updated solver build.",
      "dataVintage": "2025-10-17T00:00:00Z",
      "format": "CSV",
      "source": "FDA Generic Blood Pump Hemolysis Consortium, internal test report TR-2025-044"
