      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed; GCI for NIH is 3.1%, exceeding the 2% threshold. Near-wall y+ sensitivity study shows moderate dependence of hemolysis scalar on first-cell height in high-shear impeller passages."
