      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH) is the direct regulatory metric for hemolysis acceptance; model outputs map one-to-one to the clinical decision threshold.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary regulatory QoI per ASTM F1841 and the FDA guidance. The CFD model outputs volumetric hemolysis scalar integrated to NIH directly. QoI relevance is fully established."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
